--- !u!114 &1008417464
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1008417461}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: dbefc55dcf6fd4242a5ebcd31ba89c98, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  finalQuestions:
  - questionInfo: Which of the following statements is true about diastereomers?
    questionChoices:
    - They have identical physical properties such as melting points  and solubility.
    - They are mirror images and non-superimposable.
    - They are non mirror images stereoisomers and non superimposable.
    - They rotate plane-polarized light in opposite directions by the  same amount.
    correctChoice: They are non mirror images stereoisomers and non superimposable.
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A 31-year-old woman, who has two healthy children, notes that she
      has  had no menstrual periods for the past 6 months, but she is not pregnant 
      and takes no medications. Within the past week, she has noted some  milk production
      from her breasts. After nearly hitting a bus while  changing lanes driving
      her vehicle, she is concerned with her vision. An  optometrist finds her lateral
      vision to be reduced. On physical  examination she is afebrile and normotensive.
      Which of the following  laboratory test findings is most likely to be present
      in this woman?
    questionChoices:
    - Increased serum cortisol
    - Lack of growth hormone suppression
    - Increased serum alkaline phosphatase
    - Hyperprolactinemia
    correctChoice: Hyperprolactinemia
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A 47-year-old woman feels a 'lump' in her neck that she didn't
      notice 5  months before. Her physician's assistant palpates a firm nodule 2
      cm in  size to the left of midline in the region of the thyroid gland. By 
      scintigraphic scanning this nodule appears 'cold' with normal activity in 
      the surrounding normally sized thyroid gland. Which of the following is  the
      most likely diagnosis?
    questionChoices:
    - Papillary carcinoma
    - Follicular adenoma
    - Granulomatous thyroiditis
    - Hashimoto thyroiditis
    correctChoice: Follicular adenoma
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A patient diagnosed with thiamin deficiency exhibited fatigue and
      muscle  cramps. The muscle cramps have been related to an accumulation of 
      metabolic acids. Which one of the following metabolic acids is most likely
      to  accumulate in a thiamin deficiency?
    questionChoices:
    - Isocitric acid
    - Pyruvic acid
    - Succinic acid
    - Malic acid
    correctChoice: Pyruvic acid
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: "A 36-year-old woman comes to the office due to firm, nontender 
      swelling of her right cheek for the past 4 months. She\u2019s not a smoker
      a  drinks a wine glass almost every night. Physical examination shows  fullness
      of the preauricular space on the right side. If left untreated, this  patient
      is most likely to develop which of the following?"
    questionChoices:
    - Bitemporal hemianopsia
    - Facial droop
    - Facial numbness
    - Horner syndrome
    correctChoice: Facial droop
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: The product of the p53 antioncogene is a nuclear protein that regulates 
      DNA replication and prevents the proliferation of cells with damaged  DNA.
      It does this by stopping the cell cycle at which point?
    questionChoices:
    - Between G1 and S
    - Between G2 and M
    - Between M and G1
    - Between S and G2
    correctChoice: Between G1 and S
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: the loop of Henle plays an important role in concentrating urine
      by generating  a hypertonic medullary interstitium in a process called countercurrent 
      multiplication. Which of the following is true regarding the loop of Henle?
    questionChoices:
    - 64-80% of sodium is reabsorbed in the loop of henle
    - The thick ascending loop of henle is impermeable to sodium
    - "The Na\u2014K-2Cl channel is located on the apical surface of cells in the 
      thick ascending loop of henle"
    - The Na/Ca exchanger on the thin limb increases the calcium  reabsorption
    correctChoice: "The Na\u2014K-2Cl channel is located on the apical surface of
      cells in the  thick ascending loop of henle"
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'Highest incidence of antibiotic associated pseudo membranous 
      colitis has been noted with the use of:'
    questionChoices:
    - Chloramphenicol
    - Vancomycin
    - Clindamycin
    - Gentamycin
    correctChoice: Clindamycin
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'Which of the following drugs will be absorbed to the LEAST extent 
      in the stomach:'
    questionChoices:
    - Aspirin (pKa = 3.5)
    - 'Warfarin (pKa =5) '
    - 'Phenobarbital (pKa = 7.4) '
    - Propranolol (pKa = 9.4)
    correctChoice: Propranolol (pKa = 9.4)
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which of the following classes of adrenergic agents has utility
      in  the management of hypertension?
    questionChoices:
    - Alpha1 Agonist
    - Alpha 2 Agonist
    - 'Beta1 Agonist '
    - 'Beta3 Agonist '
    correctChoice: Alpha 2 Agonist
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A patient who received a non depolarizing neuromuscular blocker 
      (NMB) for skeletal muscle relaxation during surgery is experiencing mild  skeletal
      muscle paralysis after the surgery. Which drug could reverse  this effect of
      NMBs?
    questionChoices:
    - Pilocarpine
    - Bethanechol
    - Neostigmine
    - Atropine
    correctChoice: Neostigmine
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'Wrong about Norma Verticalis (looking at the skull from above): '
    questionChoices:
    - Coronal suture seperates frontal bone from parietal bones
    - Bregma is the site of the posterior fontanelle
    - ' Lambdoid suture separates parietal bones from occipital bone'
    - 'Sagittal suture is between the parietal bones '
    correctChoice: Bregma is the site of the posterior fontanelle
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Your patient is a 30-year-old man with persistent watery diarrhea 
      for 2 weeks. He is HIV antibody positive with a CD4 count of 10. Routine  stool
      culture revealed no bacterial pathogen. Ova and parasite analysis  revealed
      cysts that stained red in an acid-fast stain. Of the following,  which one
      is the most likely cause of this infection?
    questionChoices:
    - Cryptosporidium hominis
    - Entamoeba histolytica
    - Giardia lamblia
    - Trichomonas vaginalis
    correctChoice: Cryptosporidium hominis
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'An 11-year-old boy develops a mild fever and pain in his upper 
      arm. A radiograph of his arm shows a lytic lesion (dissolution) in the  upper
      part of the humerus with periosteal elevation over the lesion. The  patient
      is taken to surgery, where the lesion is debrided (dead bone and  pus removed).
      Culture from the lesion yields gram-positive cocci. A test  shows that the
      organism is a Staphylococcus and not a Streptococcus.  Based on this information,
      you know the organism is:'
    questionChoices:
    - Susceptible to nafcillin
    - 'A producer of protein A '
    - 'Encapsulated '
    - Catalase positive
    correctChoice: Catalase positive
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Tetanus toxin (tetanospasmin) diffuses to terminals of inhibitory
      cells  in the spinal cord and brainstem and blocks which of the following?
    questionChoices:
    - Release of acetylcholine
    - Cleavage of SNARE proteins
    - Release of inhibitory glycine and y-aminobutyric acid
    - Activation of acetylcholine esterase
    correctChoice: Release of inhibitory glycine and y-aminobutyric acid
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A 2-month old boy is evaluated for failure to thrive. His parents
      state  the child used to breast feed regularly but has fed only intermittently
      for the  past week. On exam, a murmur is heard best at the left 2nd intercostal
      space. There is a loud S2. Peripheral pulses are bounding. Pulse pressure is 
      widened. Which of the following conditions is most likely in this child?
    questionChoices:
    - Aortic coarctation
    - Atrial septal defect
    - Ventricular septal defect
    - Patent ductus arteriosus
    correctChoice: Patent ductus arteriosus
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: "A 38-year-old primigravid woman comes to the office at 18 weeks 
      gestation due to palpitations and pelvic pressure. She has been consistent 
      with prenatal care. She is following a healthy diet and takes prenatal vitamins 
      daily. Temperature is 37.5\xB0C (99.5\xB0F), pulse is 110/min, and blood pressure
      is  130/80 mmHg. On physical examination, uterus size is consistent with 22 
      weeks of gestation. Laboratory tests show hCG concentrations of 110,000  mIU/mL.
      TSH is 0.1 \u03BCU/mL. An abdominal ultrasound is obtained and shown  below.
      Further evaluation would most likely reveal which of the following karyotypes?"
    questionChoices:
    - 46, XX
    - 47, XY+21
    - 69, XYY
    - 46, XO
    correctChoice: 46, XX
    questionImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 0160aaca786683d4cb88d250e1ac34a2, type: 3}
  - questionInfo: A 49-year-old woman has had increasing cold intolerance, weight 
      gain of 4 kg, and sluggishness over the past two years. A physical  examination
      reveals dry, coarse skin and alopecia of the scalp. Her  thyroid is not palpably
      enlarged. Her serum TSH is 11.7 mU/L with  thyroxine of 2.1 micrograms/dL.
      A year ago, anti-thyroglobulin and anti thyroid peroxidase autoantibodies were
      detected at high titer. Which of   the following thyroid diseases is she most
      likely to have?
    questionChoices:
    - DeQuervain disease
    - Papillary carcinoma
    - Hashimoto thyroiditis
    - Multinodular goiter
    correctChoice: Hashimoto thyroiditis
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A 45-year-old man presents with a several-month history of weakness 
      in his lower and upper extremities. On examination, in addition to weakness 
      in multiple muscle groups, he demonstrates atrophy, hyperreflexia,  spasticity
      of the legs, and bilateral Babinski signs. Fasciculations in multiple  muscles
      are also noted. His sensation to pain, temperature, and joint  position sense
      appear intact. What is his most likely diagnosis?
    questionChoices:
    - 'Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) '
    - Vitamin B12 deficiency
    - Anterior spinal artery syndrome
    - Central cord syndrome
    correctChoice: 'Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) '
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A patient with asthma was prescribed a 32 agonist for acute relief
      of  bronchospasm, but did not respond to treatment. Which drug is the most 
      likely next option for this patient?
    questionChoices:
    - Benztropine
    - Ipratropium
    - Oxybutynin
    - Physostigmine
    correctChoice: Ipratropium
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: People with red hair, who have a mutation in the MC1R gene and
      are  homozygous for this mutation, produce high levels of which of the following 
      molecules, derived from which amino acid?
    questionChoices:
    - Eumelanin, which is a derivative of tyrosine
    - Pheomelanin, which is a derivative of tyrosine
    - Eumelanin, which is a derivative of tryptophan
    - Pheomelanin, which is a derivative of tryptophan
    correctChoice: Pheomelanin, which is a derivative of tyrosine
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which of the following lipids is prominent in cardiac tissue and
      known  for its antioxidant properties?
    questionChoices:
    - Ethanolamine plasmalogen
    - Cardiolipin
    - Lecithins
    - Inositid
    correctChoice: Ethanolamine plasmalogen
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Regarding protine-DNA interaction, which of the following amino
      acid  characteristics would most likely enhance the specificity of these  interactions,
      and where would it mostly happen ?
    questionChoices:
    - Hydrophobic side chains, minor groove
    - Positively charged side chains, major groove
    - Aromatic side chains, major groove
    - Polar uncharged side chains, major groove
    correctChoice: Positively charged side chains, major groove
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'A 10-year-old child presents with a sore throat for the past 3
      days,  accompanied by a mild headache, fatigue, and fever. On examination,
      he has  petechiae on the hard and soft palates with swollen tonsils. He was 
      suspected to have pharyngitis and was treated with ampicillin. Subsequently, 
      he developed a widely scattered maculopapular rash. The patient is most  likely
      infected with:'
    questionChoices:
    - 'Streptococcus pyrogens '
    - Epstein Barr virus
    - Enteroviruses
    - Neisseria gonorrhoeae
    correctChoice: Epstein Barr virus
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: The production of estrogen involves coordinated enzymatic activities 
      between the theca and granulosa cells of the ovarian follicle. Which of the 
      following most appropriately describes the function of estrogen?
    questionChoices:
    - Facilitates the development of internal and external genitalia
    - Produces thick cervical mucous
    - Prevents endometrial hyperplasia
    - Decrease myometrial excitability in pregnancy
    correctChoice: Facilitates the development of internal and external genitalia
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: In an experiment, it is observed that chronic, increased exposure
      to  ionizing radiation results in damage to cellular DNA. As a consequence,
      a  protein is now absent that would arrest the cell in the G1 phase of the
      cell  cycle. Subsequent to this, the cell is transformed to acquire the property
      of  unregulated growth. The absent protein is most likely the product of which
      of  the following genes?
    questionChoices:
    - RAS
    - TP53
    - MYC
    - ABL
    correctChoice: TP53
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'Hemolysis following sulfonamide therapy is most likely due to:'
    questionChoices:
    - Methemoglobin reductase deficiency
    - 'G-6-PD deficiency '
    - Vitamin K epoxide reductase deficiency
    - Thiopurine methyltransferase deficiency
    correctChoice: 'G-6-PD deficiency '
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: "48-year-old female visits your office complaining that she has
      trouble  swallowing solids and liquids has persistent, bad breath, and sometimes 
      wakes up with food on her pillow. Manometry studies show an absence of  functional
      peristalsis and failure of the lower esophageal phincter to relax  upon swallowing.
      The patient\u2019s disorders is associated with damage to which  of the following?"
    questionChoices:
    - lamina propria
    - Submucosa
    - "Myenteric (Auerbach\u2019s) plexus"
    - "Submucosal (Meissner\u2019s) plexus"
    correctChoice: "Myenteric (Auerbach\u2019s) plexus"
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  quizUIobj: {fileID: 609381637}
  timerObj: {fileID: 1273828348}
